%h1 Typography

%h3 Scale & basic styles
%p Too many type sizes and styles at once can wreck any layout. A typographic scale has a limited set of type sizes that work well together along with the layout grid. The basic set of styles are based on a typographic scale of 12, 14, 16, 20 and 34.
%br
%h3 Line height
%p To achieve proper readability and appropriate pacing, line heights have been determined based on each style’s individual size and weight. Line wrapping only applies to Body, Subhead, Headline, and the smaller Display styles. All other styles should exist as single lines.

